      "message": "[low] Line 47: 🟡 Suggestion: Using `typeof visibility !\u003d\u003d \"undefined\"` is a JavaScript-style guard that works in QML but is somewhat fragile. If `visibility` is expected to come from a parent `Window` or `ApplicationWindow`, a more idiomatic QML approach would be to check whether the component actually has a `Window` ancestor, e.g.:\n```suggestion\n    readonly property bool isFullScreen: Window.window ? Window.window.visibility \u003d\u003d\u003d Window.FullScreen : false\n```\nThis makes the intent clearer (we\u0027re checking if there\u0027s an enclosing window) rather than relying on `typeof` which could mask other issues like typos in the property name. However, the current fix is functionally correct for suppressing the test warning when `MessageBar` is instantiated outside a `Window`.",
